rComments:
Professor Kazi is amazing and kind. He takes time to answer your question and address all your concerns. He respects students. He makes sure students have a good foundation before starting a topic.
He posted recorded lectures before class time and discussed some questions in class. His quizzes included most of the questions discussed in class.

Very good prof! If you pay attention in class, the exams and quizzes are very easy. Overall, this class has a very light workload and I recommend taking it with him, as he is very sweet and accessible after class.

Kazi is a respectable professor and I believe his reviews don't do him justice. He is always available outside class and is receptive to feedback. If you want to do well, read over the slides and the textbook a few times and make sure you understand your mistakes on the quizzes, since the same questions appear on the midterm and final. Good luck!

Con: he gives 5 pop quizzes during the course Pro: these questions can be accessed after the quizzes and are usually on the midterm/final midterm and final was all multiple choice, pretty straightforward. If you have the chance, take this prof. He isn't a bad prof at all and has a good teaching method with a lot of examples.
teacherRatingTags: ['Beware of pop quizzes', 'Gives good feedback', 'Clear grading criteria']

rComments: 70 MINUTES FOR FOUR PAGES HANDWRITE FINAL EXAM

Professor Ahmed's quizzes are way too long for the given time. The midterms and final exams are long too. The lectures were too short and not in great enough detail, he just ends up reading the textbook maker's slides and you end up having to read the textbook which was poorly written to begin with.

Not sure I would recommend this professor - lectures consists of him reading off of the slides, this class is riddled with so many equations and formulas, and all he does is tell us the formulas without telling us where to use them. Difficult.

solid prof. holds lots of question sessions for students. explains concepts well/clearly. class is somewhat disorganized (doesn't give dates for the quizzes and reminds you on short notice, pushed hw due dates without telling class, syllabus says respondus but we never used it). quizzes are kinda annoying. exam is easy and has qs from the quizzes.

Plenty of quizzes and homework assignments so you can make up bad marks, but not too many that they're time-consuming and annoying. Very willing to explain concepts to students and holds plenty of Q&A sessions. Also records those sessions if you don't want to attend. One of the better ECON profs at UOttawa.
